featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
The ancient name of talisman is 'Perinjalur'. That is what is found in the works and documents found. Chellur. It was also known as Lakshmipuram and Kotampuram.
Considered the stronghold of the Malayalam Brahmins, Perinchalur was the only early inhabitant of Brahmins who were devotees of Shiva.
Then in 1320, at the beginning of the month of Singham, a deadly epidemic broke out in the principality of Perinjalur and many of the close relatives of the then king died. Despite the application of various treatment methods, there was no cure. Following this, the doshaparihara member brought from Mangalapuram raised the issue and to resolve the issue with the Kalantas (disciples of Zainuddin Makhdum known by the Persian name 'Kalantan' who were the disciples of Sufi tradition. Kalantas are famous for their medicine and Atubhuta Siddhi) of Muhammadan or Muslim roots.
It was suggested to seek help. According to that, the king's followers brought four Muslim families from Dharmadam with a lot of money, land and all other help. Among them was the Thangal family who came from Yemen. It was these families rooted in the tradition of the Kalantas who saved the village of Perinjalur from Maravyadi. The Hindu community firmly believed that all the prosperity of Perinjalur was due to the Muslims brought from Dharmadam and maintained good relations with them.
Thaliparamb Juma Masjid was built by four families who came from Dharmadam
The Thaliparamba Great Jamaat Mosque is the mecca of the Thaliparamba locals
The city of Taliparamba grew up around this church.
The church was built around 1302. Four families lived around it and earned their livelihood. After many years, in 1817, the church was renovated and built keeping the old style. Till 1932, the church was ruled by four Tharavat Karanavars. As registered with the Waqf Board in 1960, the mosque had 400 acres of land.

There are classes for young children and also for secondary and post secondary levels.  The old building was very cute with a spiral ladder and all.   But it was demolished a few years and new concrete thing has come in its place.  The Madrassa has its own small mosque inside with a little pond attached to it. A government school called G.M.U.P. can be seen alongwith the Madrassa.

featured_reviews.review_id: Manna Makham has a sylvan atmosphere with many tree branches intertwining into intricate designs of shade.  Some parts of the compund are so much filled with tree branches that any one above four feets tall cannot walk comfortably. The graves of the holy men appear to grow a few inches every year. There is a holy well here where virgins used to get gold ornaments if they lowered a bucket while chanting prayers. A gentleman from Tamil Nadu has opened a prayer center opposite the Dargah and he offers herbal medicines for the devotees.
